      • linkTaskWithExternal

        public WorkplanMapping linkTaskWithExternal(WorkPlanIntegrationContext context,
                                            WorkplanMapping workplanMapping,
                                            ValueSet values)
        Callback when a task is Mapped to an external application in the PPM work plan.
        The WorkplanMapping object containing the linked task mapping configuration is passed to the method, and can be modified there before being returned, for example by adding extra config information that would only be generated in this callback method.
        By default, this method does nothing and returns the WorkplanMapping object unmodified.

        You can check the Agile Manager Connector for an example of using this callback to save information of newly created Release.

        Parameters:
        context - Work plan integration context
        workplanMapping - linked task mapping configuration
        values - Values of user-input fields of associated workspace, which will contain the information to connect to the external application.

      • getAgileEntityInfoFromMappingConfiguration

        public LinkedTaskAgileEntityInfo getAgileEntityInfoFromMappingConfiguration(ValueSet values)
        Get Agile Entity information for the linked task from the task's mapping configuration. Implement this method when agile data is synced to PPM and you want join PPM project and task data with the synced agile data.
        Parameters:
        values - The field values of task integration mapping
        Returns:
        the Agile Entity information for the linked task from the task's mapping configuration
        See Also:

      • getCustomDetailPage

        public java.lang.String getCustomDetailPage()
        URL of the page, which will be displayed on the tab "Hybrid Project" in task detail page.
        For example, /itg/integrationcenter/ppm-connector-impl-web/sub-project-detail.jsp
        It is null by default.

      • supportTimesheetingAgainstExternalWorkPlan

        public boolean supportTimesheetingAgainstExternalWorkPlan()
        This is a flag to tell whether this connector support user log timesheet on external task. If it is true, connector developer should make sure that all the external tasks contain an unique Id among the whole external workplan. That means each class that implements ExternalTask should override the method getId().
        Returns:
        support timesheeting indicator
